# Binary file types — never apply EOL conversion.
#
# core.autocrlf=true (Windows default) would otherwise silently
# rewrite LF→CRLF on checkout, corrupting files whose byte offsets
# matter — most painfully PDFs whose xref tables encode absolute
# byte positions. Without these rules the PR-DOCUSIGN-1 step 5
# placeholder PDF would break on the next Windows checkout / reset.
#
# Coverage rationale:
#   *.pdf       — contract templates, generated reports, fixtures
#   *.png /     — LIA licence uploads accept PNG and JPG per
#   *.jpg /       PR-DOCUSIGN-1 step 3's image-widening; matches the
#   *.jpeg        backend allowlist so any future committed asset
#                 (logo, doc screenshot, etc.) inherits the rule.
#   *.ttf       — Caladea (SIL OFL 1.1) bundled under
#                 backend/assets/fonts/ for PR-DOCUSIGN-1 step 5g
#                 engagement-letter LIA-identity stamping; any TTF
#                 corruption would crash font embedding at runtime.

*.pdf  binary
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.ttf  binary
